<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEEKEND TV; LENA HORNE TAKES THE SPOTLIGHT ON A&E 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A concert by Lena Horne, a new children's series from Nickelodeon and a 
special for men about prostate health highlight the viewing options this 
weekend. 
</P>
<P>
 "An Evening With Lena Horne," taped last September at the Supper Club in 
Manhattan, features tunes from her most recent CD and old favorites such as 
"The Lady Is a Tramp" and "Just One of Those Things."The program will be shown 
at 5 and 9 p.m. Sunday on A&E. 
</P>
<P>
 "U to U" is billed by Nickelodeon as an interactive series in which youngsters 
can play games and respond to poll questions in between new cartoons and film 
shorts. It premieres on the cable channel at 6 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
 Dr. Peter Scardino is the host of "Straight Talk on Prostate Health," a 
90-minute program about male sexual dysfunction and diseases of the prostate 
gland, airing at 4 p.m. today on KCET-TV Channel 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
