<P>
SWEDISH TEACHER FIRED FOR UNDRESSING IN CLASS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A teacher who undressed in front of her adult class to demonstrate a lesson 
has resigned under pressure -- despite protests from her students. 
</P>
<P>
 Irene Wachenfeldt, 44, was teaching a group of unemployed women how important 
it is to love your own body. To drive home the point, the mother of five 
undressed, a newspaper report said. 
</P>
<P>
 Students wrote a letter to the school principal protesting the decision to 
fire Wachenfeldt. "It was one of our best lessons. . . . It helped boost our 
self-confidence," student Jenny Berg was quoted as saying. 
</P>
