<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An express train headed from eastern Hungary to Budapest derailed Friday and 
slammed into a station building, killing at least 21 people. 
</P>
<P>
 At least 60 people were injured, National Police spokesman Laszlo Garamvoelgyi 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred at Szajol, about 40 miles southeast of the Hungarian 
capital, when the second car of an express train derailed and dragged three 
other cars off the tracks. The overturned carriages smashed into the station 
building, railway officials said. 
</P>
