<TEXT>
<P>
 Whirlpool Subject of Justice Department Probe: The appliance maker's stock 
fell in heavy trading after word leaked out that it was being investigated by 
federal antitrust authorities.The leaker was its jilted former customer, Best 
Buy. County Natwest analyst Nicholas Heymann said the probe could make it 
difficult for Whirlpool to raise prices, something the company needs to do to 
protect its profits. Whirlpool spokeswoman Robin Skiles said the company 
decided to stop selling its Whirlpool brand through Best Buy because Best Buy 
operates largely as a discount warehouse operation and this conflicts with 
Whirlpool's strategy. 
