against it and ordered that Nintendo must also pay Alpex Computer Corp. a 
percentage of infringing revenues. U.S. District Judge Kimba Wood refused 
Nintendo's motion for a new trial. Instead, she said, Nintendo must pay the 
damage award to Alpex, a defunct Colorado company, along with 6% of Nintendo's 
infringing revenues during the period between Dec. 1, 1992, and May 31, 1994, 
