<TEXT>
<P>
 Dayton Hudson Moving 500 Jobs Out of California: Dayton Hudson Corp. will 
consolidate the credit operations of its Mervyn's and department store 
divisions in Minneapolis, moving the jobs to Minnesota from California, the 
company said.The 500 workers at Mervyn's headquarters in Hayward, Calif., will 
be offered a chance to relocate, the company said. Dayton Hudson said the cost 
of the consolidation will result in a fourth-quarter pretax charge of about $10 
million, or 8 cents per share, but will result in significant future savings. 
The current Minneapolis credit operation also serves Target Stores, which 
Dayton Hudson owns along with Marshall Fields, Dayton's and Hudson's department 
stores. 
</P>
