<HEADLINE>
<P>
IMAGINE VITALE AFTER A POT OF COFFEE; PREP FOOTBALL: TEXAS ANNOUNCERS GET 
NATIONAL ATTENTION AFTER THEY THROW OUT OBJECTIVITY AND GET A LITTLE TOO 
EXCITED DURING PLAYOFF GAME. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The football game was phenomenal -- 34 points were scored in the final 2 1/2 
minutes -- and the TV announcers weren't bad, either. 
</P>
<P>
 The delivery of last Saturday night's John Tyler-Plano East high school 
playoff has brought national attention to mailman-anchor Denny Garver, his 
co-host, Eddy Clinton, and their guest for the evening, Lake Highlands High 
Coach Mike Zaffuto. 
</P>
<P>
 "The game got out of hand, and we got out of hand even more," Garver said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sound bites from the play-by-play for Plano Telecable have been rebroadcast 
from New York to Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 Plano East scored 27 points in the final 2 minutes 33 seconds to take the lead 
with 24 seconds remaining, then lost when its final kickoff was returned for 
the winning touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 "They got it again! They got it again! . . . This is unbelievable. . . . Good 
gosh a'mighty Joe Friday," Garver said after Plano East had recovered an onside 
kickoff after scoring. "Somebody give me something. I'm gonna die." 
</P>
<P>
 Garver after Plano East had scored again, taking the lead at 44-41: "Everybody 
on their cars in the radio back to Plano, you've done missed the greatest 
comeback of all times! Of all times!" 
</P>
<P>
 Zaffuto, however, had the big call. 
</P>
<P>
 "Oh no! Oh no! Oh no! Oh my gosh, no! Come on! No! No! Gosh!" he said as the 
97-yard kickoff return unfolded. "God bless those kids. I am sick. I want to 
throw up." 
</P>
</TEXT>
