<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; RAMS; ROCKER WANTS TO FEEL WANTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 What has happened to defensive tackle David Rocker? 
</P>
<P>
 Rocker, who received a guaranteed contract to re-sign with the Rams this 
season, has spent the season on the bench.Even when the team has suffered 
injuries up front, it has turned to rookie free agent D'Marco Farr before 
calling on Rocker. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm not angry or bitter, but if I'm not wanted here, then I think it would be 
better for me to move on next season and play elsewhere," Rocker said. "I still 
have great confidence in my ability to play, and sitting 16 games straight on 
the bench won't change those feelings." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive tackle Jimmie Jones, listed as probable on the team's injury report, 
has been unable to practice this week because of a sprained ankle. Jones tried 
to run Friday but reported pain. 
</P>
<P>
 In the first meeting with the Saints this year, New Orleans took advantage of 
Sean Gilbert's absence at defensive tackle and ran a season-high 38 times. The 
Saints, who rank last in the league running, gained 118 yards. T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
