<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROBYN NORWOOD , From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Oleg Tverdovsky, the Mighty Ducks' second pick overall at the NHL draft in 
June, has received medical clearance from team and will play Canadian junior 
hockey with the Brandon Wheat Kings starting next week. 
</P>
<P>
 Tverdovsky, 18, missed the exhibition season because of a groin injury, and 
General Manager Jack Ferreira assigned him to Brandon of the Western Hockey 
League because he is eager for the young defenseman to play as the NHL lockout 
drags on. Tverdovsky would rejoin the Ducks should the labor dispute be 
resolved. 
</P>
<P>
 Tverdovsky also is likely to play for Russia in the World Junior Championships 
Dec. 26-Jan. 4 at Red Deer, Canada. ROBYN NORWOOD 
</P>
</TEXT>
