</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UCLA, USC and Long Beach State women's volleyball teams begin play this 
weekend in the NCAA tournament, each grouped in a different regional. 
</P>
<P>
 Each had a first-round bye and will play host for a second-round match.UCLA 
(28-3) will play host to Georgia Tech (26-8) in Pauley Pavilion and USC (20-7) 
will play host to New Mexico (20-9) in the Lyon Center. Both matches begin at 7 
tonight. Long Beach (25-5) will play host to Montana (25-5) Sunday at 3 p.m. in 
the Pyramid. 
</P>
<P>
 But after this weekend, if they survive, the three schools will go their 
separate ways. 
</P>
