<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: GUERRERO A MINOR LEAGUE ANGEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BOB NIGHTENGALE , From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Angels, after learning that Bo Jackson has declined an invitation to 
rejoin them, have decided to gamble on another power hitter. 
</P>
<P>
 Would you believe . . . Pedro Guerrero? 
</P>
<P>
 Guerrero, 38, who has spent the last two seasons playing for Sioux City, Iowa, 
of the Northern (Independent) League, agreed to a triple-A contract Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Although his offer does not include an invitation to their major league 
spring-training camp, sources say Guerrero could be used as a replacement 
player if the strike continues into the spring. 
</P>
<P>
 Guerrero, who has been out of the big leagues since 1992, spent 12 years in 
the Dodger organization before being traded to St. Louis in 1988. 
</P>
<P>
 Also Friday, free-agent closer Lee Smith provided a counterproposal to the 
Angels. Negotiations are continuing. BOB NIGHTENGALE 
</P>
</TEXT>
