<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL / CITY SECTION SEMIFINALS; CRENSHAW TAKES BIG RISKS BUT 
STOPS DORSEY ANYWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LONNIE WHITE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With a seven-point lead and the ball deep in its own territory late in the 
fourth quarter, Crenshaw High twice chose not to punt on fourth-and-one 
situations. 
</P>
<P>
 Daring for most, but not for the Cougars as they twice gained the needed 
yardage to help them hold on to a 26-19 victory over Dorsey in the City 4-A 
semifinal Friday night at Fremont High. 
</P>
<P>
 Farrel Payton, who gained 98 yards in 19 carries, rushed for the key first 
downs on both plays. Crenshaw (12-1), which kept the ball for seven of the 
final eight minutes, finally punted to the Dons, whose last drive ended on an 
interception by Johnny Johnson as time expired. 
</P>
<P>
 After a high-scoring first half, the game turned defensive in the second half. 
Dorsey twice drove deep into Crenshaw territory only to come away empty, thanks 
to a key tackle by Kabeer Smith and an overthrown pass by Dorsey. 
</P>
<P>
 Crenshaw, however, ended the scoring drought with a halfback option pass by 
Seals, who finished with 97 yards in 23 carries, to Magee, who caught five 
passes for 157 yards and two touchdowns. LONNIE WHITE 
</P>
</TEXT>
