HIGH SCHOOL FOOTBALL / CITY SECTION SEMIFINALS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bell 27, Manual Arts 7 -- Bell, seeking its first championship since 1984, 
scored two touchdowns within a five-minute span in the fourth quarter to secure 
the victory in the 3-A semifinal game at Gardena High. 
</P>
<P>
 Vern Benard rushed for 142 yards in 28 carries, including a 79-yard touchdown 
run to give the Eagles (10-3) a 20-7 lead with eight minutes to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Raul Saldana and Freddy Alcala each had interceptions for Bell, which stopped 
Manual Arts (9-4) on downs three times inside the 20. 
</P>
