<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; UC IRVINE FALLS WHEN THOMAS' SHOT DOESN'T 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine's Tamera Thomas missed a free throw with 1.9 seconds left that could 
have tied the score in the Anteaters' 72-71 loss to Notre Dame in the first 
round of the UCI/Marriott Classic Friday at the Bren Center. 
</P>
<P>
 Allah-Mi Basheer led the Anteaters (0-3) with 20 points.She scored their last 
field goal with 2 minutes 24 seconds left to give Irvine a 70-68 lead. But 
Notre Dame's Carey Poor scored four consecutive points to give the Irish a 
72-70 lead with 1:25 left. 
</P>
<P>
 Thomas was fouled by Kari Hutchinson with 1.9 seconds left, then made the 
first of two free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Poor had 21 points for Notre Dame (1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Golden State Athletic Conference preseason women's basketball 
tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Concordia 77, Azusa Pacific 65 -- Michelle Krank scored 22 points for the 
Eagles, who advanced to play Northwest Nazarene in the final today. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Redlands men's basketball tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Chapman 82, Menlo 69 -- Stefan Mumaw scored 22 points for Chapman (3-1), which 
advances to play host Redlands in the championship game tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 In the UC Irvine Speedo Cup swimming: 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA wins four events -- UCLA women won four individual swimming events Friday 
in the second day of the competition at Belmont Plaza Pool in Long Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Annette Salmeen started the Bruin run winning the 100-yard butterfly in 56.04 
seconds. The other three victories came from Megan Oesting in the 200 freestyle 
(1:50.91), Lindsay Etter in the 100 breaststroke (1:03.63) and Jill Jenkins in 
the 100 backstroke (56.16). 
</P>
</TEXT>
