<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; LOARA UPSETS NO. 8 ORANGE ON PENALTY KICK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jonathan LeProux scored on a penalty kick with five minutes remaining to give 
host Loara a 1-0 upset of Orange, the eighth-ranked team in Orange County, in a 
nonleague boys' soccer game Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Jose Sanchez recorded eight saves in his first shutout for Loara (1-0). Orange 
is 0-0-1. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague boys' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Brethren Christian 3, Magnolia 1 -- Matt Mullins scored two unassisted goals 
and Sean Reeves added the third for visiting Brethren Christian. 
</P>
<P>
 Kevin Price had 17 saves for Brethren Christian (1-0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley 1, Woodbridge 0 -- Joey Vasquez scored the winning goal with 
seven minutes left, helping Fountain Valley (3-0) remain undefeated.  
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 1, Katella 0 -- Alejandro Sanchez scored the winning goal 20 minutes 
into the second half for Fullerton (1-0-1). Michael Shumaker had seven saves to 
record his second consecutive shutout. 
</P>
<P>
 Newport Harbor 4, Estancia 1 -- Justin Kerr scored four goals in the first 
half to lead visiting Newport Harbor (3-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Santiago 5, Costa Mesa 0 -- Albert Mendez scored two goals for visiting 
Santiago (2-0). Erik Bautista, Victor Ruiz and Horacio Rivera also scored. 
</P>
<P>
 Sonora 5, Anaheim 3 -- Wes Hale scored three goals, leading visiting Sonora 
(2-0). Sal Torres scored twice for Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
 Valencia 1, El Dorado 0 -- Martin Aguilar scored in the first half for 
visiting Valencia (1-1). Stephen Huerth had nine saves for the shutout. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Harold S. Young boys' soccer tournament in Clovis: 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 1, Bakersfield 0 -- Steve Braud scored a goal in the first 
half off an assist from Ruben Villalobos for Capistrano Valley (3-0). In an 
earlier game against Fresno Edison, Brett Thompson scored two goals and Ryan 
Hawkins added one to give the Cougars a 3-0 victory. Capistrano Valley advanced 
to the eight-team finals today. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonleague girls' soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei 3, Claremont 1 -- Kristie Hoback, Kim Buccola and Katie Ticehurst 
had goals for host Mater Dei (1-0-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park 3, Century 0 -- Tiffany Peach, Gabby Fagins and Teresa Flores 
scored goals for host Buena Park (2-0). 
</P>
</TEXT>
