<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL TENNIS; BASICA KEEPS STREAK GOING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Junior Amanda Basica became the third consecutive Palos Verdes Peninsula High 
player to win the girls' Southern Section individual singles tournament with a 
6-2, 6-2 victory over Santa Barbara San Marcos junior Kara Warkentin on Friday 
at the Lindborg Racquet Club in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 Basica, the tournament's top-seeded player, had her serve broken once in each 
set, but she was never pressed by the unseeded Warkentin.In the morning 
semifinals, Basica defeated fourth-seeded Monique Allegre of Camarillo, 6-3, 
6-0, and Warkentin beat Sanaz Ghazal of Temecula Valley, 6-3, 4-6, 7-6. 
</P>
<P>
 Warkentin chose to try to slug it out with Basica from the baseline. It wasn't 
the best of strategies against the world's 12th-ranked player in the girls' 18 
division. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought maybe she might come into the net off the deep balls she hit, but 
she played the same the whole match," said Basica, who reached the section 
finals as a freshman. 
</P>
<P>
 In the doubles final, Santa Barbara junior Pilar Montgomery and freshman 
Sarita Yardi defeated Corona del Mar juniors Megan Wachtler and Alissa Scott, 
6-3, 6-0. The third-seeded Montgomery and Yardi won the last nine games of the 
match over the fourth-seeded team. DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
