<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOORPARK MEETS DEANZA IN STATE SOCCER SEMIFINAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRENE GARCIA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Moorpark College women's soccer team will play in the state final four 
tournament this weekend at Cosumnes River College in Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
 The Raiders (11-3-3) face De Anza College (16-1-1) in today's 2 p.m. 
semifinal. 
</P>
<P>
 De Anza, the defending state champion, is the No. 1 team from the Coast 
Conference. Moorpark finished second in the Western State Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark is led by forward Vanessa Macen, who has scored 12 goals, defender 
Summer Salvatera and midfielder Heather Heit. All were named to the 
all-conference team. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark goalkeeper Amy Fisher has 73 saves and six shutouts. Backup goalie 
Shannon Henry has 36 saves and four shutouts. 
</P>
<P>
 "We don't have any one top player," Moorpark Coach Ken Dale said. "The big key 
with this team has been sticking together through thick and thin." 
</P>
<P>
 WSC champion Bakersfield (13-4-1) plays Santa Rosa (14-2-1), winner of the Bay 
Valley Conference, in the other semifinal today at 11. 
</P>
<P>
 The championship game is scheduled for Sunday at 11 a.m. 
</P>
