COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 3 STUDENTS TO RECEIVE ART DAVIS SCHOLARSHIPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three Orange County college students will receive scholarships ranging from 
$50 to $200 from a nonprofit group seeking to promote higher education. 
</P>
<P>
 Winners of the Art Davis Scholarships, sponsored by the Better Advantages for 
Students and Society, a Corona del Mar nonprofit group, will receive the awards 
at a ceremony from noon to 4 p.m. Sunday at the Holiday Inn, 17941 Karman Ave., 
Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners are Cyndi O'Brien, a music student at Orange Coast College; Stacy 
Holland, who is working on a master's degree in psychology at Cal State 
Dominguez Hills, and Corey Schribner, a music student at Fullerton College. 
</P>
<P>
 The scholarships are presented in the name of Art Davis, a music teacher at 
Orange Coast College for the past seven years. He helped found BASS more than a 
year ago to foster interest in education and encourage college students to 
complete their studies. 
</P>
<P>
 Davis said that the idea for a scholarship was started by his students four 
years ago, who wanted to present him with a birthday gift. He said the scholars 
are selected by a three-member panel, which includes himself, based on 
interviews and a 500-word essay about their goals. 
</P>
<P>
 Applications forms are available at colleges and universities in Southern 
California, Davis said. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets for Sunday's awards ceremony are $25 each, which includes lunch and 
entertainment.BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</TEXT>
