<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ANAHEIM; SCHOOL TRUSTEES MIGHT FILL VACANCY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By and DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Members of the Anaheim Union are expected to fill a vacancy on the board by 
making a temporary appointment. 
</P>
<P>
 The vacancy was created when trustee Lou Lopez was elected to the Anaheim City 
Council last month, two years short of the end of his term. The board will vote 
Monday on whether to appoint someone to fill the vacancy or to hold a special 
election. A special election would cost about $125,000 and could not be held 
until June. 
</P>
<P>
 If the board decides to appoint someone to complete Lopez's term, it will 
probably do so by Jan. 31. District officials are recommending that 
applications be accepted until Jan. 5. and DANIELLE A. FOUQUETTE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
