includes eight sophomores; four are returning starters. Mendoza, who didn't 
play last season because of a broken wrist, is the only upperclassman and 
should earn a starting position early. Harris is optimistic about her team's 
future, although she knows this season is just a starting point. "Next year we 
could do some damage." If she can keep this roster together for three years, 
Harris could have a league champion. 
