averaged 11 points and 10 rebounds to lead the team. They will also miss 
Lindsey Etheridge, who was fourth in the county in assists, averaging nearly 
six. Bradberry averaged 10 points last season and will need to grab some 
rebounds to make up for Shaffner's loss. Olivier will join the team after 
sitting out last season because of a ruptured Achilles' tendon she received 
playing volleyball. Crary will play off-guard and is the Eagles' main outside 
scoring threat. Shelton plays an inside game, but would love to multiply his 
options by getting some long-distance production. 
</P>
