</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
1994-95 GIRLS' BASKETBALL / SMALL SCHOOLS; EXPRESS LEAGUE; BETHEL BAPTIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 1993-94 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 4-15 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 4-10 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Jeff Higgins 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-0 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Melody 
Cantrell Sr. 5-6 F Rachael Farrokh Sr. 5-7 F Janel Mullikin Jr. 5-8 C Kimberly 
Williams Jr. 5-4 G 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Adrian Cortez Fr. 
5-2 G 04,20,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Jennifer Barber So. 5-2 G Megan 
Freel Fr. 5-7 F Jerveta Spearman Fr. 5-4 F Elizabeth Williams Fr. 5-8 F OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Higgins takes over at Bethel Baptist, replacing Wanda Garcia, whose teams went 
6-33 in two years. Higgins might have a little better luck because four 
starters return from last season's team. Height is the main concern for Bethel 
Baptist, which has no true center. The tallest player in the lineup is 5-foot-8 
Mullikin, who starts for the second consecutive year at post. Cantrell, Farrokh 
and Williams also return for their second season as starters. The Warriors will 
need to play tough defense to make up for their lack of size. Along with the 
experience of their starting four, the Warriors are also bringing in a 
promising group of freshmen who should be able to help them improve on last 
season's fifth-place finish. 
</P>
<P>
 SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 December 5-10 at Cougar Classic tournament; 13 at Harbor City Gateway 
Christian; 16 vs. Heritage Christian. 
</P>
<P>
 January 3 vs. Norwalk Pioneer Baptist; 10 at Huntington Beach Claremont; 13 at 
South Gate Southeast Lutheran; 14 vs. Long Beach Gethsemane; 17 at Downey 
Calvary Chapel; 21 vs. Harbor City Gateway Christian; 24 at Heritage Christian; 
27 at Norwalk Pioneer Baptist; 28 vs. Rolling Hills Prep; 31 at Rolling Hills 
Prep. 
</P>
<P>
 February 3 vs. Huntington Beach Claremont; 7 at Long Beach Gethsemane; 11 vs. 
Downey Calvary Chapel. 
</P>
