</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
1994-95 GIRLS' BASKETBALL / SMALL SCHOOLS; ACADEMY LEAGUE; ST. MARGARET'S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 1993-94 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 16-2 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 8-0 
</P>
<P>
 COACH: Brady Lock 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 32-20 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Lisa 
Bevill Jr. 5-8 F Jean Freeman Jr. 5-10 F Shay Trette Jr. 5-8 G 04,20,05,06,04 
TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Marianne Bergheim Sr. 6-0 C Stephanie Canright Jr. 5-5 
G Kelly Dane Sr. 5-10 F Kristen Helms Sr. 5-8 F Jenny Schutt Sr. 5-6 G 
04,17,05,06,04 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. HGT. P Gina Arreola So. 5-6 G Christy Averill 
So. 5-7 G OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 With the transfer of Capistrano Valley Christian into the league, it will not 
be easy for St. Margaret's to repeat as league champions. The Eagles were the 
only team St. Margaret's lost to last season. The Tartans graduated only two 
starters from last season's squad and they return seven lettermen. Trette, a 
first-team all-league selection, returns for her junior season after leading 
the team in scoring last season (11-point average). Lock will look to Trette to 
open up the inside game with her outside shooting. Freeman will need to put the 
ball up more under the basket and improve her scoring from last season, when 
she average eight points. Lock hopes his team's pressure defense will force 
turnovers and get the Tartans running in a quick transition game. 
</P>
<P>
 SCHEDULE 
</P>
<P>
 December 7 vs. Tri-City Christian; 9 vs. Cerritos Whitney; 10 vs. Encino Holy 
Martyrs; 13 at La Canada Flintridge Prep; 15 at La Jolla Country Day. 
</P>
<P>
 January 3 vs. Laguna Beach; 6 vs. Liberty Christian; 10 at Connelly; 13 vs. 
Capistrano Valley Christian; 18 vs. Fontana Ambassador Christian; 20 vs. 
Liberty Christian; 24 at Connelly; 28 at Capistrano Valley Christian. 
</P>
<P>
 February 3 at Liberty Christian; 7 vs. Connelly; 10 vs. Capistrano Valley 
Christian. 
</P>
